//! Second module exporting a DISTINCT type that happens to share the bare name
//! `CloseError` with `hew::closableerr`. Used by the cross-module trait-sig
//! reject oracle: an `impl Closable` whose `close` returns
//! `closableerr2.CloseError` does NOT satisfy a trait that requires
//! `closableerr.CloseError` — two distinct nominal types from two modules, not
//! one type spelled two ways. The signature comparison must reject this at the
//! type boundary rather than collapse both bare names and accept it.

/// A distinct error type with the same bare name as `closableerr.CloseError`.
pub type CloseError {
    detail: i64;
}
